<TITLE> Ex-minister Omar, ex-DAB chief Hossain get bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 1 (bdnews24.com) - The High Court has granted bail to former state minister for law Shahjahan Omar and Doctors Association of Bangladesh leader AZM Zahid Hossain in separate cases involving of illegal wealth. The bench of justices Mohammad Abdul Wahab Miah and Mohammad Marzi-Ul-Haque gave the bail orders upon their separate petitions. The two were granted bail on separate petitions until their appeals against lower court convictions are settled. The High Court also heard their appeals against the verdicts. A special court in Dhaka sent Omar to jail on May 7 this year after his surrender by order of the High Court. The court had sentenced him to 13 years on May 15 last year. Another special court to which former DAB president Hossain surrendered on May 13 this year had sentenced him to 13 years in jail on May 25 last year. Senior advocate Khandaker Mahbub Hossain stood for Omar and advocate Ahsanul Karim for Hossain, while assistant attorney general Runa Nahrin represented the state. b
